<content type="html" xml:base="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/viewtopic.php?t=6441&amp;p=28226#p28226"><![CDATA[
Okay so, for anyone who needs some extra confidence, I got hit by it. I was stupid and didn't stop when the digital signature wasn't there. Though I did acknowledge it by thinking &quot;wasn't this signed last time I updated? Oh well.&quot;<br />Unfortunately for me, something else happened when I got infected. Avast, my antivirus, caused me to bluescreen due to an incompatibility with the Anniversary update on newer Intel CPUs. So even when I fixed my master boot record, I was stuck in a boot loop and had no idea what to do.<br /><br />But the only reason I discovered the boot loop is because I fixed my master boot record, and it's really easy.<br />I simply borrowed a family member's laptop to make myself a boot disk (just download the Windows ISO of your system and slap it on a disk or USB drive), used it to get into the recovery environment for Windows, opened the command prompt, and used the command &quot;bootec /fixmbr&quot;. That got me to the windows loading screen, which gave me a BSOD every time because of Avast. <br /><br />All in all, don't panic. The boot record is really easy to fix with little technical knowledge, and none of your personal files will be tampered with.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=4885">Crawfish</a> — Thu Aug 04, 2016 5:18 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
</entry>
